cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialogue safety. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training a model to become robust to human attacks. Additionally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with offensive language in public forums and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it addresses the need to guard against adversarial behavior in human interactions.
